<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>West Virginia Claims Morgantown Regional Title</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/baseball-west-virginia-claims-morgantown-regional-title</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/baseball-west-virginia-claims-morgantown-regional-title</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The West Virginia baseball team poses for a photo after winning the Morgantown Regional" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/2/060126_BSB_Kentucky_NCAAT_GB-11.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – For the third consecutive season, the West Virginia University baseball team advanced to the NCAA Super Regionals as the Mountaineers defeated Kentucky, 6-5, in 10 innings, Monday evening at Kendrick Family Ballpark to win the Morgantown Regional.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/060126_BSB_Kentucky_NCAAT_GB-11.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/060126_BSB_Kentucky_NCAAT_GB-11.jpg"><media:title>The West Virginia baseball team poses for a photo after winning the Morgantown Regional</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/060126_BSB_Kentucky_NCAAT_GB-11.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 2 Jun 2026 00:49:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59156</s:story_id></item><item><title>Baseball Fans, Savor These Special Moments</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/baseball-fans-savor-these-special-moments</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/2/baseball-fans-savor-these-special-moments</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="West Virginia fans celebrate the Mountaineers' walk-off, 6-5 victory over Kentucky in the deciding game of the Morgantown Regional played at Kendrick Family Ballpark on Monday, June 1, 2026." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/2/Celebration-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – I'm old, and watching college baseball games these last couple of days has made me feel much older.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/Celebration-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/Celebration-Main.jpg"><media:title>West Virginia fans celebrate the Mountaineers' walk-off, 6-5 victory over Kentucky in the deciding game of the Morgantown Regional played at Kendrick Family Ballpark on Monday, June 1, 2026.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/2/Celebration-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 2 Jun 2026 08:58:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59157</s:story_id></item><item><title>Bridgeport’s McDougal Seizes Opportunity to Extend West Virginia’s Season</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/baseball-bridgeports-mcdougal-seizes-opportunity-to-extend-west-virginias-season</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/baseball-bridgeports-mcdougal-seizes-opportunity-to-extend-west-virginias-season</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="West Virginia players celebrate winning pitcher Ben McDougal's five-inning relief stint in the Mountaineers' 11-9 victory over Kentucky to set up a deciding game five on Monday at Kendrick Family Ballpark in Morgantown, W.Va." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/1/McDougal2-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – During a long, 12-hour day when West Virginia pounded out 23 hits and 21 runs in victories over Wake Forest and Kentucky, you knew for the Mountaineers to keep their postseason hopes alive, somebody in a gold-colored jersey was going to have to man-up on the pitching mound.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/McDougal2-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/McDougal2-Main.jpg"><media:title>West Virginia players celebrate winning pitcher Ben McDougal's five-inning relief stint in the Mountaineers' 11-9 victory over Kentucky to set up a deciding game five on Monday at Kendrick Family Ballpark in Morgantown, W.Va.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/McDougal2-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 1 Jun 2026 00:32:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59153</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Rally to Defeat Kentucky and Force Game Seven</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/baseball-mountaineers-rally-to-defeat-kentucky-and-force-game-seven</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/baseball-mountaineers-rally-to-defeat-kentucky-and-force-game-seven</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Paul Schoenfeld hits a home run against Kentucky in the NCAA Regional" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/1/WVU_v_WAKE_2026_Sunday_Regional-226.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team scored five runs in the top of the ninth to defeat Kentucky, 11-9, Sunday evening and force a game seven. First pitch against the Wildcats on Monday is set for 6 p.m.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/WVU_v_WAKE_2026_Sunday_Regional-226.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/WVU_v_WAKE_2026_Sunday_Regional-226.jpg"><media:title>Paul Schoenfeld hits a home run against Kentucky in the NCAA Regional</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/WVU_v_WAKE_2026_Sunday_Regional-226.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 1 Jun 2026 00:04:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59152</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU’s Tavon Austin, Jim Carlen on 2027 NFF College Football Hall of Fame Ballot</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/wvus-tavon-austin-jim-carlen-on-2027-nff-college-football-hall-of-fame-ballot</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/wvus-tavon-austin-jim-carlen-on-2027-nff-college-football-hall-of-fame-ballot</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tavon Austin, scoring one of his four touchdowns against Clemson in the 2012 Discover Orange Bowl, is listed on the ballot for the 2027 College Football Hall of Fame." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/1/Austin-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Electrifying West Virginia University All-American wide receiver Tavon Austin is a first-time designee on the ballot for this year's College Football Hall of Fame released by the National Football Foundation (NFF) earlier today.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/Austin-Main.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/Austin-Main.jpg"><media:title>Tavon Austin, scoring one of his four touchdowns against Clemson in the 2012 Discover Orange Bowl, is listed on the ballot for the 2027 College Football Hall of Fame.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/Austin-Main.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 1 Jun 2026 11:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59155</s:story_id></item><item><title>Baseball NCAA Morgantown Regional Information</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/27/baseball-ncaa-morgantown-tournament-information</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/27/baseball-ncaa-morgantown-tournament-information</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Morgantown Regional Tournament Information" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/26/NCAA_Landing_Page_Header_WITH_BioPrecision.jpg" /><br /><br />]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/26/NCAA_Landing_Page_Header_WITH_BioPrecision.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/26/NCAA_Landing_Page_Header_WITH_BioPrecision.jpg"><media:title>Morgantown Regional Tournament Information</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/26/NCAA_Landing_Page_Header_WITH_BioPrecision.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 09:24:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59135</s:story_id></item><item><title>Parking Info for Monday’s Baseball Game</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/parking-info-for-mondays-baseball-game</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/1/parking-info-for-mondays-baseball-game</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Medicine lot tailgating" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/1/IMG_3039.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The following is updated parking info for Monday's baseball game between West Virginia and Kentucky.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/IMG_3039.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/IMG_3039.jpeg"><media:title>Medicine lot tailgating</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/1/IMG_3039.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 1 Jun 2026 10:13:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59154</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Defeat Wake Forest to Advance to Regional Final</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/31/baseball-mountaineers-advance-to-regional-final</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/31/baseball-mountaineers-advance-to-regional-final</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Dawson Montesa" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/31/053126_BSB_WF_NCAAT_GB-10.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team advanced to the Morgantown Regional final with a 10-5 victory over two-seed Wake Forest, Sunday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers will play Kentucky at 5 p.m. tonight and will have to win to force a winner-take-all game seven on Monday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/31/053126_BSB_WF_NCAAT_GB-10.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/31/053126_BSB_WF_NCAAT_GB-10.jpg"><media:title>Dawson Montesa</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/31/053126_BSB_WF_NCAAT_GB-10.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 31 May 2026 16:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59151</s:story_id></item><item><title>Three Mountaineers Advance to NCAA Outdoor Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/track-field-three-mountaineers-advance-to-ncaa-outdoor-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/track-field-three-mountaineers-advance-to-ncaa-outdoor-championships</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Joy Naukot competing in the 10,000 meters at the NCAA East First Round" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University track and field team qualified three student-athletes for the NCAA Outdoor Championships following competition at the NCAA East First Round in Lexington, Kentucky.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg"><media:title>Joy Naukot competing in the 10,000 meters at the NCAA East First Round</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/IMG_1354.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 23:01:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59150</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Fall to Kentucky</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/baseball-mountaineers-fall-to-kentucky-2026</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/30/baseball-mountaineers-fall-to-kentucky-2026</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Gavin Kelly rounds the bases after hitting a home run against Kentucky." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/30/WVU_v_UK_2026_Regional-71-2.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University baseball team fell to Kentucky, 11-9, in the NCAA Regional winner's bracket game. The Mountaineers fall to 40-15 and will play Wake Forest in an elimination game on Sunday at 12 p.m. The Wildcats improve to 33-21 and advance to the regional final on Sunday at 5 p.m.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/WVU_v_UK_2026_Regional-71-2.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/WVU_v_UK_2026_Regional-71-2.jpeg"><media:title>Gavin Kelly rounds the bases after hitting a home run against Kentucky.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/30/WVU_v_UK_2026_Regional-71-2.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 21:41:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59149</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>